cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.DS

This paper deals with the detection of malicious data in vehicular ad hoc networks, which is a topic related to network security and communication protocols. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also discusses the use of a model of expected driver behavior, which involves artificial intelligence techniques, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) a likely category as well. The paper also deals with the detection of Sybil attacks, which is a type of attack on decentralized systems, making cs.SY (Systems and Control) another likely category. Additionally, the paper involves simulation experiments, which could fall under cs.DS (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). Finally, since the paper deals with the security of vehicular ad hoc networks, it could also be categorized under cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
